Like Frank, I have also declined all interviews. My work is in the lab and
not on some talk show. The reason that progress is continuing to be made is
that serious researchers keep away from publicity and stick to what they do
best.



I also applaud the efforts of members here who work on alternate and
inexpensive methods of building communications devices. This is the true
work of the pioneer. By efforts such as these progress in ITC will continue
to be made.



Ron R.



From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Frank Sumption
Sent: Sunday, November 25, 2007 11:56 PM
To: evp-itc@yahoogroups.com
Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] C2C




 So far I have been declining all interviews. I think I&#39;ve my work by
helping to get these various methods started. I have not said absolutely no,
but I don&#39;t like attention, and don&#39;t like public speaking. 

 Frank-S

  _____  

To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
From: duck@...
Date: Sun, 25 Nov 2007 22:51:03 -0700
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] C2C

Frank,



Are you going to be on C2C next month? 

I heard that in the Edge of darkness  chat room.



-Sum



----- Original Message ----- 

From: Frank Sumption &lt;mailto:franks-boxes@...&gt;  

To: evp-itc@yahoogroups.com 

Sent: Sunday, November 25, 2007 10:43 PM

Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Translating?




 It&#39;s just practice, and that opens up your senses. We use various methods
of using &quot;raw&quot; audio, or providing something that the entities can make
voices out of. These techniques bring the &quot;voices&quot; up to a level of actual
communications, sometimes two way. 

 Frank-S




